    <article id="article" class="" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/Article">
    
    <h1 class="headline" itemprop="name">An Awkward Question for Robert Gates: Has the Deep State Taken Over?</h1>

    
            <div class="dek" itemprop="description">
            The former secretary of defense believes that the uniformed military &quot;had taken control of the policy process&quot; during the war in Afghanistan.        </div>
    
    <div class="metadata">
        <span class="authors"><a href="http://www.theatlantic.com/conor-friedersdorf/" class="author" itemprop="author" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person" rel="author" >Conor Friedersdorf</a></span>        <span class="date"><time datetime='2014-01-09T07:30:00-05:00' itemprop="datePublished" content="2014-01-09T07:30:00-05:00">Jan 9 2014, 7:30 AM ET</time></span>
    </div>

    <div style="clear:both"></div>

